{
  "text": "Hey, want to see something cool? If this isn't cool, both figuratively and literally, then I don't know what is. It's all made of snow! One of the big reasons I wanted to come here to Harbin was to check out the Ice and Snow Sculpture Festival. It's actually the biggest one of its kind in the world. So I'm currently at Sun Island, which is the location for the Snow Sculpture Exhibition, and they are amazing. They're beautiful, they're intricate, they're huge. So I'm going to check this out here first before I go and check out the other venues of the festival. Oh yeah, did I fail to mention? This here is only one section of the entire Harbin Snow and Ice Festival. We're going to be doing a lot of walking today. Harbin, like many of the other cities in Dongbei, has the Songpa River running right through it. In Harbin here, it's completely frozen over from November to April every year. Actually, I'm standing on it right now! But here in Harbin, this frozen river is a huge source of entertainment just in itself. I'm going to try out this banana boat thing. It seems to be tied to a car, so I feel it could only be fun. Oh my god, oh my god, oh my god! Oh my god, this is so fun! There's one thing that happens here on the Songhua River that I've been dying to see with my own eyes. Let's go see if we can find it. Welcome to China's coldest swimming pool! This is a tradition passed down by the Edo people. The Edo people in Dongfang, Xiaobadi, passed down the Edo culture and the Edo dance in Harbin. Why are you doing this? It's good for your health. It's good for your health, so you won't get sick. It can also help with a lot of chronic diseases. Like cardiovascular diseases, and it's good for your back and neck. Do you like it? Yes! Why? It's good for your health. You won't get sick. You'll get younger and younger. How old are you? Ninety-six. What?! Furious respect for these guys. I have no idea how they are able to get into that water in this freezing cold temperature. Keep in mind it's currently minus 25 degrees. Okay, I seem to have gotten myself a little bit distracted here on the Songhua River. Time to get myself to my next destination on the other side. So now that we've already checked out the sculptures made of snow, it's time that we come here and check out the sculptures made out of ice. This here is Ice and Snow World, and it covers an area of 600,000 square meters, and it's made up of over 2,000 massive ice carvings. It's honestly the most impressive thing. Check this out! I just keep wondering how many people are needed to build all of these structures. Wow, 10,000 people, 15 days to build all of this. It just still doesn't seem enough. Even though this place is super beautiful during the day, I've been told that the best time of day to come is after the sun sets, and I guess we'll soon see why. Oh my god. Yeah, this is absolutely breathtaking. And the scale of it, it's just colors everywhere. It's literally like being in a fairy tale. Thank you guys so much for joining me on this Dongbei adventure. I have had so much fun. I've seen things that I've never seen before, and things that I'll probably never see again. I would recommend anyone come here to Dongbei, just make sure that you prepare for some seriously cold weather. Anyway, I hope you've enjoyed these videos, and I'll see you next time. Bye guys!",
